<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Lighten Privacy Policy</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for Lighten, a macOS app for reducing file size locally on your Mac.">
  <style>
    :root {
      color-scheme: light dark;
      --bg: #f7f7f8;
      --card: rgba(255,255,255,.78);
      --text: #151518;
      --muted: #62626a;
      --line: rgba(0,0,0,.10);
      --accent: #0a84ff;
    }

    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
      :root {
        --bg: #08080a;
        --card: rgba(255,255,255,.06);
        --text: #f4f4f5;
        --muted: #a0a0aa;
        --line: rgba(255,255,255,.12);
        --accent: #5aa9ff;
      }
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(10,132,255,.12), transparent 36rem),
        var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "SF Pro Text", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    main {
      width: min(860px, calc(100% - 32px));
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 56px 0;
    }

    article {
      background: var(--card);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 24px;
      padding: clamp(24px, 5vw, 48px);
      box-shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,.08);
      backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 48px);
      line-height: 1.08;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    }

    h2 {
      margin: 34px 0 10px;
      font-size: 20px;
      line-height: 1.25;
      letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    }

    p, li { font-size: 16px; }
    p { margin: 0 0 14px; }

    ul {
      margin: 8px 0 16px;
      padding-left: 22px;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .meta {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    .notice {
      margin: 24px 0;
      padding: 16px 18px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 16px;
      background: rgba(127,127,127,.08);
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    footer {
      margin-top: 36px;
      padding-top: 20px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 14px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <article>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: May 15, 2026</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Lighten</strong> handles information.
        Lighten is a macOS app designed to reduce the size of images, PDFs, and videos
        directly on your Mac.
      </p>

      <div class="notice">
        <strong>Summary:</strong> Lighten processes your files locally on your Mac.
        Your files are not uploaded to our servers, and the app does not track you.
      </div>

      <h2>1. Local File Processing</h2>
      <p>
        Lighten works locally on your Mac. When you choose, drag, drop, or save a file,
        the app uses local macOS technologies to create a smaller copy of that file.
      </p>
      <p>
        Your original files remain on your device unless you choose to move, delete, or
        modify them yourself. Lighten is designed to create reduced copies without
        changing your originals.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Files You Select</h2>
      <p>
        Lighten only accesses the files and folders that you explicitly select through
        macOS file pickers, drag-and-drop, or save dialogs. The app uses those files only
        to perform the requested file size reduction and to save the resulting copy.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not receive, store, upload, sell, or share the contents of your files.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Data Collection</h2>
      <p>
        Lighten does not collect personal data through the app. The app does not use
        third-party analytics, advertising SDKs, tracking SDKs, or account systems.
      </p>
      <p>Lighten does not collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your files or file contents</li>
        <li>Your photos, videos, PDFs, or documents</li>
        <li>Usage analytics</li>
        <li>Advertising identifiers</li>
        <li>Location data</li>
        <li>Contact lists</li>
        <li>Browsing history</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Internet Connection</h2>
      <p>
        Lighten does not require an internet connection to reduce files. File reduction
        is performed on-device.
      </p>
      <p>
        The app may include external contact links, such as a feedback email link.
        Opening those links may use your email app or browser outside Lighten.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Feedback and Support Emails</h2>
      <p>
        If you choose to contact us by email, we will receive the email address you use
        and any information you choose to include in your message. We use this information
        only to respond to your request, provide support, improve the app, or investigate
        reported issues.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        Lighten does not include third-party analytics, third-party advertising, or
        third-party tracking services inside the app.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Payments and App Store</h2>
      <p>
        If Lighten is distributed through the Apple App Store, Apple may process purchases,
        downloads, subscriptions, refunds, and related App Store activity according to
        Apple's own privacy practices and policies. We do not receive your full payment
        card details from Apple.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Lighten is not designed to knowingly collect personal information from children.
        Because the app does not collect personal data through the app, we do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children through Lighten.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell, rent, or share personal data collected through Lighten because
        Lighten does not collect personal data through the app.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Security</h2>
      <p>
        Lighten is designed to minimize privacy risk by processing files locally and not
        uploading them to our servers. However, no software or system can be guaranteed
        to be completely secure.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make changes, we will
        update the “Last updated” date at the top of this page.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions, feedback, or bug reports, you can contact us at:
        <a href="mailto:lighten@matisandoval.com">lighten@matisandoval.com</a>
      </p>

      <footer>
        Lighten Privacy Policy
      </footer>
    </article>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
